(45, 2, 3, 40, 23, 33, 33, 'escape the judgment of God', 'Judgment and Damnation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and the consequences of hypocrisy. Both passages emphasize the inability to escape divine judgment for wrongdoing.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 2, 3, 10, 10, 3, 3, 'thinkest thou this, O man', 'Judgment and Misinterpretation', 'This connection highlights the theme of misjudgment. In Romans, the idea of judging others while committing the same acts is paralleled in 2 Samuel, where the princes misinterpret David''s intentions, assuming deceit rather than honor.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 2, 3, 18, 35, 2, 2, NULL, 'Judgment and Righteousness Comparison', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of human judgment and righteousness in relation to God''s standards. Romans questions the assumption of escaping judgment while doing wrong, paralleling Job''s assertion of righteousness over God''s. This connection highlights the tension between human self-perception and divine judgment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 2, 3, 19, 50, 21, 21, 'judgest them which do such things', 'Judgment and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and accountability for one''s actions. Both passages emphasize that individuals who judge others while committing similar wrongs will face God''s reproof and judgment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
