(45, 2, 9, 26, 18, 4, 4, NULL, 'Consequences of Sin and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of sin, stating that those who do evil will face tribulation or death. Romans highlights the universal application of this principle to both Jews and Gentiles, while Ezekiel underscores God''s ownership of all souls and the fate of the sinner.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
