(45, 2, 9, 44, 13, 46, 47, 'upon every soul of man that doeth evil', 'Judgment and Salvation for All', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment upon those who do evil, as seen in Romans, and the subsequent offer of salvation to the Gentiles in Acts. Both passages emphasize the necessity of addressing the Jewish audience first before extending the message to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
