(45, 2, 17, 23, 48, 1, 2, 'makest thy boast of God', 'Identity and Boasting in God', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of the people of God and their reliance on Him. Romans highlights the boasting in the law, while Isaiah critiques those who mention God but lack truth and righteousness.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 2, 17, 66, 2, 9, 9, 'thou art called a Jew', 'Identity of True Jews', 'This connection highlights the distinction between those who claim Jewish identity and their true standing before God. Both passages emphasize the concept of being a Jew in relation to faithfulness to God''s law and the implications of false claims to that identity.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
