(45, 2, 25, 48, 6, 15, 15, NULL, 'Circumcision and New Creation', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of circumcision in relation to the law and its ultimate irrelevance in Christ. Romans highlights that circumcision is only beneficial if the law is kept, while Galatians states that neither circumcision nor uncircumcision matters, but rather being a new creature.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
