(45, 2, 25, 45, 2, 23, 23, 'the law', 'Law and Circumcision Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of keeping the law. Romans 2:25 indicates that circumcision is only beneficial if the law is upheld, while Romans 2:23 questions the value of boasting in the law if one breaks it.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 2, 26, 51, 2, 11, 11, 'circumcision be counted for circumcision', 'Circumcision and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of circumcision as a symbol of righteousness. Both passages emphasize the significance of spiritual circumcision and the righteousness that comes from faith, rather than mere physical observance.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
