(45, 2, 26, 45, 8, 4, 4, 'righteousness of the law', 'Righteousness of the Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteousness in both passages. Romans 2:26 discusses the righteousness of the law being applicable to the uncircumcised, while Romans 8:4 emphasizes that this righteousness is fulfilled in those who walk after the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 2, 26, 23, 56, 6, 7, 'uncircumcision be counted for circumcision', 'Inclusivity of God''s Covenant', 'This connection highlights the acceptance of those outside traditional boundaries, as both passages emphasize that righteousness and covenant relationship with God are available to all, not just the circumcised. Romans speaks to the uncircumcised being counted as righteous, while Isaiah promises acceptance for the ''sons of the stranger'' who join themselves to the Lord.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 2, 26, 40, 8, 11, 12, 'righteousness of the law', 'Righteousness and Inclusion', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteousness and inclusion in the kingdom of heaven. Both passages emphasize that those considered outsiders, like the uncircumcised, can attain righteousness and sit with the patriarchs, while those who are traditionally seen as insiders may be excluded.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 2, 26, 40, 15, 28, 28, 'righteousness of the law', 'Faith and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of faith leading to righteousness. In Romans, the emphasis is on the righteousness of the law being accessible to the uncircumcised, while in Matthew, the woman''s faith results in her daughter''s healing, showcasing that faith can transcend traditional boundaries.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 2, 26, 44, 10, 2, 4, 'righteousness of the law', 'Righteousness and Acceptance', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that righteousness can be recognized by God regardless of physical circumcision. Romans discusses the uncircumcised keeping the law, while Acts highlights Cornelius, a devout uncircumcised man, whose prayers and alms are accepted by God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 2, 27, 40, 12, 41, 42, 'judge thee, who by the letter', 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment based on righteousness rather than mere adherence to the law. Both passages emphasize that those who fulfill God''s requirements, regardless of their background, will judge those who do not.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 2, 27, 45, 2, 29, 29, NULL, 'Inward vs. Outward Circumcision', 'This connection highlights the contrast between outward circumcision and inward circumcision of the heart. Both passages emphasize the importance of fulfilling the law beyond mere external compliance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
