(45, 4, 13, 45, 9, 8, 8, NULL, 'Connection of Promise and Heirship', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''children of the promise.'' Romans 4:13 discusses the promise made to Abraham, while Romans 9:8 clarifies that true heirs are those counted as children of the promise, not merely of the flesh.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 13, 19, 2, 8, 8, 'heir of the world', 'Inheritance and Possession Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of inheritance in both passages. Romans 4:13 speaks of Abraham''s promise as an heir, while Psalms 2:8 mentions the heathen as an inheritance.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 13, 48, 3, 16, 18, NULL, 'Promise and Inheritance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the promise made to Abraham and his seed, highlighting that it is through faith rather than the law. Romans 4:13 states the promise is through ''the righteousness of faith,'' while Galatians 3:18 affirms that the inheritance is by promise, not law.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 13, 19, 72, 11, 11, 'heir of the world', 'Heirship and Universal Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority and inheritance. Romans speaks of Abraham''s promise to be an heir, while Psalms emphasizes that all nations will serve him, suggesting a universal dominion tied to that heirship.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 14, 48, 3, 18, 24, 'faith is made void', 'Connection of Law and Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the law and the promise made to Abraham. Romans 4:14 states that if the law is the basis for inheritance, faith is rendered ineffective, which parallels Galatians 3:18''s assertion that the inheritance is by promise, not law.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 14, 50, 3, 9, 9, 'faith is made void', 'Connection of Righteousness and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between righteousness derived from the law and that which comes through faith. Romans 4:14 suggests that reliance on the law nullifies faith, while Philippians 3:9 highlights righteousness through faith in Christ.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 14, 23, 55, 11, 11, 'void', 'Connection of Voids in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the concept of being ''void.'' Romans 4:14 discusses faith being made void if the law is the basis for inheritance, while Isaiah 55:11 emphasizes that God''s word will not return void but will accomplish its purpose.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 14, 45, 3, 31, 31, 'made void', 'Faith and the Law', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between faith and the law. Romans 4:14 suggests that if the law is the basis for inheritance, faith loses its significance, while Romans 3:31 asserts that faith does not nullify the law but rather establishes it.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 14, 45, 4, 16, 16, 'faith is made void', 'Connection of Faith and Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in relation to the promise. Romans 4:14 states that if heirs are based on the law, faith is void, while Romans 4:16 clarifies that the promise is assured through faith, not just the law.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 14, 48, 2, 21, 21, NULL, 'Connection of Law and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of relying on the law for righteousness. Romans 4:14 states that if heirs are based on the law, faith is void, while Galatians 2:21 asserts that if righteousness comes by the law, then Christ''s sacrifice is in vain.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 14, 58, 7, 19, 19, 'the law be heirs', 'Connection of Law and Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the limitations of the law in relation to faith and hope. Romans 4:14 suggests that the law nullifies the promise, while Hebrews 7:19 states that the law made nothing perfect, indicating a need for a better hope.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 15, 45, 5, 13, 13, 'there is no transgression', 'Connection of Law and Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between law and sin. Romans 4:15 states that where there is no law, there is no transgression, which is echoed in Romans 5:13, indicating that sin is not imputed without law.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 15, 48, 3, 10, 10, 'the law worketh wrath', 'Connection of Law and Curse', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of the law. Romans highlights that the law leads to transgression and wrath, while Galatians states that those under the law are cursed for failing to uphold it.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 15, 45, 3, 19, 20, 'there is no transgression', 'Law and Transgression Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the law in revealing sin and establishing guilt. Romans 4:15 states that where there is no law, there is no transgression, while Romans 3:19-20 highlights that the law brings knowledge of sin and makes the world guilty before God.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 15, 46, 15, 56, 56, 'there is no transgression', 'Connection of Law and Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between law and sin. Romans 4:15 states that where there is no law, there is no transgression, while 1 Corinthians 15:56 highlights that the strength of sin is the law.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 15, 43, 3, 36, 36, 'wrath', 'Connection of Wrath and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of wrath associated with transgression and unbelief. Romans 4:15 states that ''where no law is, there is no transgression,'' while John 3:36 indicates that ''the wrath of God abideth on him'' who does not believe.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 15, 48, 3, 19, 19, 'there is no transgression', 'Law and Transgression Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the law and transgressions. Romans states that where there is no law, there is no transgression, while Galatians explains that the law was added because of transgressions.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 15, 47, 3, 7, 9, 'the law worketh wrath', 'Law and Condemnation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the law in bringing condemnation and wrath. Romans highlights that where there is no law, there is no transgression, while 2 Corinthians contrasts the ministration of death with the ministration of the spirit, indicating the law''s role in condemnation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 16, 45, 3, 24, 26, 'by grace', 'Connection of Justification and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize justification through faith and grace. Romans 4:16 highlights faith as the means to receive God''s promise, while Romans 3:24-26 discusses being justified freely by grace through faith in Jesus.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 4, 16, 49, 2, 8, 8, 'by grace; to the end the promise', 'Connection of Faith and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize salvation through faith and grace. Romans highlights that faith ensures the promise, while Ephesians states that salvation is a gift of God through faith.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
