(45, 8, 2, 46, 15, 45, 45, 'law of the Spirit of life', 'Life and Spirit Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life through the Spirit. Romans speaks of freedom from sin and death, while 1 Corinthians contrasts Adam''s living soul with the quickening spirit of Christ.', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 2, 43, 8, 36, 36, 'free from the law of sin and death', 'Freedom in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of freedom found in Christ. Romans 8:2 speaks of being free from ''the law of sin and death,'' while John 8:36 declares that those made free by the Son are ''free indeed.''', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 2, 43, 6, 63, 63, 'the law of the Spirit of life', 'Connection of Spirit and Life', 'This connection highlights the role of the Spirit in granting life and freedom. Both passages emphasize that the Spirit brings life, contrasting it with the limitations of the flesh and the law of sin.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 3, 44, 13, 39, 39, NULL, 'Justification and the Law', 'This connection highlights the inability of the law to justify believers, as noted in both passages. Romans 8:3 mentions the weakness of the law through the flesh, while Acts 13:39 states that justification cannot come from the law of Moses.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 3, 48, 4, 4, 5, 'God sending his own Son', 'Connection of Redemption and Law', 'Both passages emphasize God''s sending of His Son to address the limitations of the law. Romans highlights the weakness of the law through the flesh, while Galatians speaks to the purpose of sending the Son to redeem those under the law.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 3, 58, 7, 18, 19, 'the law could not do', 'Connection of Law and Weakness', 'Both passages emphasize the weakness of the law. Romans highlights the law''s inability to achieve righteousness, while Hebrews speaks of the law''s unprofitableness and introduces a better hope. This connection highlights the transition from the old covenant to the new.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 3, 47, 5, 21, 21, 'condemned sin in the flesh', 'Connection of Sin and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Christ in addressing sin. Romans 8:3 discusses Christ condemning sin in the flesh, while 2 Corinthians 5:21 highlights Him being made sin for us, leading to our righteousness.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 3, 48, 3, 13, 13, 'the law could not do', 'Connection of Law and Redemption', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Christ in addressing the limitations of the law. Romans 8:3 discusses how God sent His Son to condemn sin in the flesh, while Galatians 3:13 highlights Christ redeeming us from the curse of the law.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 3, 58, 10, 14, 14, 'condemned sin in the flesh', 'Connection of Christ''s Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Christ''s offering in addressing sin. Romans highlights God''s action in condemning sin in the flesh, while Hebrews speaks of the perfection achieved through that one offering.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 3, 45, 6, 6, 6, 'condemned sin in the flesh', 'Connection of Sin and Flesh', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of sin being addressed through the flesh. Romans 8:3 discusses how God condemned sin in the flesh, while Romans 6:6 highlights the destruction of the body of sin, indicating a transformative relationship with sin through Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 4, 48, 5, 16, 16, 'walk not after the flesh', 'Walking in the Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of walking after the Spirit rather than the flesh. This connection highlights the fulfillment of righteousness through a Spirit-led life.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 4, 48, 5, 22, 25, NULL, 'Connection of Spirit and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize walking after the Spirit, highlighting the transformation that occurs in believers. Romans 8:4 speaks of fulfilling the law through the Spirit, while Galatians 5:25 encourages living and walking in the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 4, 51, 1, 22, 22, 'righteousness of the law might be fulfilled', 'Righteousness and Holiness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being presented as holy and unblameable through the fulfillment of righteousness. Both passages emphasize the transformation that occurs through the Spirit and the death of Christ.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 4, 49, 5, 26, 27, 'righteousness of the law', 'Righteousness and Holiness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being holy and without blemish. Romans 8:4 speaks of fulfilling righteousness, while Ephesians 5:26-27 focuses on presenting a glorious church that is holy.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 4, 58, 12, 23, 23, 'righteousness of the law', 'Righteousness and Just Men Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteousness and perfection. Romans 8:4 speaks of fulfilling righteousness, while Hebrews 12:23 refers to ''spirits of just men made perfect.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 4, 65, 1, 24, 24, 'righteousness of the law', 'Righteousness and Faultlessness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being presented faultless and fulfilling righteousness. Romans 8:4 speaks of fulfilling the law''s righteousness, while Jude 1:24 highlights being presented faultless before God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 4, 66, 14, 5, 5, 'righteousness of the law', 'Righteousness and Faultlessness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of being without fault or guile, highlighting a state of righteousness. Romans 8:4 speaks of fulfilling the law''s righteousness, while Revelation 14:5 describes those who are without fault before God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 5, 46, 2, 14, 14, 'after the Spirit', 'Connection of Spiritual Discernment', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between those who are ''after the flesh'' and those who are ''after the Spirit.'' This connection highlights how spiritual understanding is inaccessible to the ''natural man,'' who cannot comprehend spiritual matters.', 'theme', 0.6359999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 5, 48, 5, 19, 25, 'things of the flesh', 'Flesh vs. Spirit Contrast', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between the flesh and the Spirit. Romans 8:5 discusses those who mind the things of the flesh, while Galatians 5:19-25 lists the works of the flesh and contrasts them with the fruit of the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.608, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 5, 43, 3, 6, 6, 'things of the Spirit', 'Connection of Flesh and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between flesh and Spirit. Romans 8:5 discusses those who mind the things of the Spirit, while John 3:6 states that which is born of the Spirit is spirit.', 'theme', 0.58, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 5, 51, 3, 1, 3, 'things of the Spirit', 'Connection of Spiritual Focus', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of focusing on spiritual matters rather than earthly concerns. Romans 8:5 speaks of ''the things of the Spirit,'' while Colossians 3:2 urges believers to ''set your affection on things above.''', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 5, 45, 8, 6, 7, 'things of the flesh', 'Mindset and Spirituality Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between being ''after the flesh'' and being ''spiritually minded.'' This connection highlights how the mindset influences one''s relationship with God, leading to either death or life and peace.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 5, 50, 3, 18, 19, 'mind the things of the flesh', 'Connection of Flesh and Earthly Things', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between those who focus on earthly or fleshly desires and those who pursue spiritual matters. Romans highlights the mindset of the flesh, while Philippians warns against those who mind earthly things.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 5, 41, 8, 33, 33, 'the things of the Spirit', 'Connection of Flesh and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between the things of God and the things of men. Romans 8:5 speaks of those who mind the things of the Spirit, while Mark 8:33 highlights Peter''s focus on the things of men, illustrating a conflict between spiritual and earthly priorities.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 6, 48, 6, 8, 8, 'to be carnally minded is death', 'Mindset and Spiritual Reaping', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between sowing to the flesh and being spiritually minded. They highlight that a focus on the flesh leads to death or corruption, while a spiritual focus results in life and peace or everlasting life.', 'theme', 0.909, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 6, 45, 8, 7, 7, 'carnally minded is death', 'Connection of Mindset and Consequence', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between the carnal mind and spiritual mindset. The first verse states that being carnally minded leads to death, while the second explains that the carnal mind is enmity against God, highlighting the negative consequences of such a mindset.', 'theme', 0.685, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 6, 45, 8, 13, 13, 'carnally minded is death', 'Mindset and Consequences', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of living according to the flesh versus the Spirit. They highlight that a carnal mindset leads to death, while a spiritually minded life results in life and peace.', 'theme', 0.657, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 6, 59, 1, 14, 15, 'is death', 'Death and Spiritual Mindset', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of a carnal mindset leading to death. Romans highlights that being carnally minded results in death, while James explains that lust leads to sin and ultimately death.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 6, 43, 14, 27, 27, 'peace', 'Connection of Peace and Mindset', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of peace, with Romans linking a spiritually minded perspective to life and peace, while John presents peace as a gift from Jesus. This connection highlights the importance of a spiritual mindset in experiencing true peace.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 6, 48, 5, 22, 22, 'peace', 'Mindset and Spiritual Fruit', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of spiritual mindset. Romans highlights that being spiritually minded leads to life and peace, while Galatians lists peace as a fruit of the Spirit, suggesting a direct link between spiritual focus and the resulting virtues.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 6, 43, 14, 6, 6, 'life', 'Connection of Life and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''life.'' Romans 8:6 contrasts spiritual and carnal mindsets, linking spiritual mindset to life, while John 14:6 identifies Jesus as ''the life,'' suggesting that true life comes through Him.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 7, 46, 2, 14, 14, 'carnal mind is enmity against God', 'Mind and Spiritual Discernment', 'Both passages emphasize the inability of the carnal or natural mind to understand spiritual truths. The ''carnal mind'' in Romans and the ''natural man'' in Corinthians highlight a shared theme of enmity against God and the lack of receptiveness to His law and Spirit.', 'theme', 0.5449999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 7, 62, 2, 15, 16, 'carnal mind is enmity against God', 'Conflict Between Flesh and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the opposition between the desires of the flesh and the will of God. Romans 8:7 highlights the enmity of the carnal mind against God, while 1 John 2:15-16 warns against loving the world and its desires, which are not from the Father.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 7, 59, 4, 4, 4, 'enmity against God', 'Enmity Against God', 'Both passages emphasize enmity against God, highlighting that a mindset aligned with the world or flesh opposes divine law. This connection illustrates the conflict between worldly desires and God''s commandments.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 7, 49, 4, 18, 19, 'carnal mind is enmity against God', 'Mind and Heart Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the state of the mind and heart in relation to God. Romans highlights the carnal mind''s enmity against God, while Ephesians describes a darkened understanding and blindness of heart, indicating a separation from God''s life.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 7, 45, 7, 22, 22, 'law of God', 'Mind and Law of God', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the carnal mind''s enmity against God and the inward man''s delight in the law of God. Both passages emphasize the differing attitudes towards God''s law, illustrating a conflict between the flesh and the spirit.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 7, 55, 3, 4, 4, 'carnal mind is enmity against God', 'Mindset Against God', 'Both passages emphasize a mindset that opposes God. The ''carnal mind'' in Romans reflects a state of being that aligns with ''lovers of pleasures more than lovers of God'' in 2 Timothy, indicating a prioritization of worldly desires over divine obedience.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 7, 58, 8, 10, 10, 'the carnal mind is enmity against God', 'Connection of Mind and Law', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the ''carnal mind'' that opposes God''s law and the promise of a new covenant where God''s laws are internalized in the mind and heart. Both passages emphasize the relationship between the mind and adherence to God''s law.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 8, 43, 3, 5, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Flesh and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between the flesh and the Spirit. Romans 8:8 states that those in the flesh cannot please God, while John 3:6 clarifies that what is born of the flesh is flesh, contrasting it with what is born of the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 8, 58, 11, 5, 6, 'cannot please God', 'Pleasing God Through Faith', 'This connection highlights that both passages emphasize the necessity of faith to please God. Romans 8:8 states that those ''in the flesh cannot please God,'' while Hebrews 11:6 asserts that ''without faith it is impossible to please him.''', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 8, 45, 7, 5, 5, 'in the flesh', 'Connection of Flesh and Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the state of being ''in the flesh'' and its consequences. Romans 8:8 states that those in the flesh cannot please God, while Romans 7:5 describes how being in the flesh leads to sinful actions that result in death.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 8, 45, 8, 9, 9, 'in the flesh cannot please God', 'Connection Between Flesh and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between being in the flesh and being in the Spirit. The first verse states that those in the flesh cannot please God, while the second affirms that believers are in the Spirit if the Spirit of God dwells in them.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 8, 51, 1, 10, 10, 'cannot please God', 'Pleasing God Through Good Works', 'This connection highlights the theme of pleasing God. Romans 8:8 states that those in the flesh cannot please God, while Colossians 1:10 emphasizes walking worthy of the Lord unto all pleasing and being fruitful in good works.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 8, 58, 13, 21, 21, 'cannot please God', 'Pleasing God Through Good Works', 'This connection highlights the theme of pleasing God through one''s actions. Romans 8:8 states that those ''in the flesh cannot please God,'' while Hebrews 13:21 emphasizes being ''wellpleasing in his sight'' through good works.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 8, 62, 3, 22, 22, 'cannot please God', 'Pleasing God Through Actions', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of actions in relation to pleasing God. Romans 8:8 states that those in the flesh cannot please God, while 1 John 3:22 highlights that keeping commandments leads to receiving from Him, indicating that pleasing God is linked to obedience.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 9, 48, 4, 6, 6, 'the Spirit of Christ', 'Connection of the Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit in believers'' lives. Romans 8:9 highlights the necessity of having the Spirit of Christ, while Galatians 4:6 speaks of the Spirit of His Son being sent into hearts, affirming their identity as God''s children.', 'theme', 0.58, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
