(45, 8, 9, 55, 1, 14, 14, 'the Spirit of God dwell in you', 'Connection of the Holy Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Spirit in believers'' lives. Romans 8:9 mentions the Spirit of God dwelling in believers, while 2 Timothy 1:14 speaks of keeping the good thing by the Holy Ghost which dwells in us.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 9, 46, 6, 19, 19, 'the Spirit of God dwell in you', 'Connection of Spirit and Body', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of the Spirit within believers. Romans 8:9 highlights the necessity of the Spirit of God dwelling in individuals, while 1 Corinthians 6:19 refers to the body as the temple of the Holy Ghost, indicating a shared theme of divine indwelling.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 9, 43, 14, 17, 17, 'the Spirit of God dwell in you', 'Connection of the Spirit''s Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the indwelling of the Spirit. Romans 8:9 speaks of the Spirit of God dwelling in believers, while John 14:17 mentions the Spirit dwelling in them. This connection highlights the transformative role of the Spirit in the lives of believers.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 9, 45, 8, 11, 11, 'the Spirit of God dwell in you', 'Connection of the Spirit''s Role', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the Spirit dwelling in believers. The first verse states that having the Spirit of God is essential for belonging to Christ, while the second verse connects this indwelling Spirit to the resurrection power that quickens mortal bodies.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 9, 48, 5, 24, 24, 'the Spirit of God dwell in you', 'Connection of Spirit and Flesh', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between the Spirit and the flesh. Romans 8:9 highlights the necessity of the Spirit of God, while Galatians 5:24 speaks to the crucifixion of the flesh, indicating a transformation in those who belong to Christ.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 10, 49, 3, 17, 17, 'Christ be in you', 'Connection of Christ''s Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of Christ within believers. Romans highlights that Christ in us brings life, while Ephesians speaks of Christ dwelling in our hearts, suggesting a transformative relationship through faith.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 10, 48, 2, 20, 20, 'the Spirit is life because of righteousness', 'Connection of Life in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the transformative power of Christ in believers. Romans 8:10 speaks of the Spirit as life, while Galatians 2:20 highlights that Christ lives in the believer, indicating a shared theme of spiritual life through faith in Christ.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 10, 47, 5, 21, 21, 'the Spirit is life because of righteousness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the transformation from sin to righteousness. Romans 8:10 speaks of life through the Spirit, while 2 Corinthians 5:21 highlights being made the righteousness of God through Christ''s sacrifice for sin.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 10, 43, 11, 25, 26, 'the Spirit is life', 'Life Through Christ''s Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life in relation to faith in Christ. Romans speaks of the Spirit as life, while John declares Jesus as the resurrection and the life, linking spiritual life to belief in Him.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 10, 43, 17, 23, 23, 'the Spirit is life', 'Connection of Life and Unity', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of Christ and the transformative power of the Spirit. Romans highlights the Spirit as life, while John speaks of unity in Christ, suggesting a shared life through Him.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 10, 45, 8, 11, 11, 'the Spirit is life because of righteousness', 'Connection of Spirit and Life', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit in relation to life and the body. Romans 8:10 states that the Spirit is life because of righteousness, while Romans 8:11 discusses the Spirit''s power to quicken mortal bodies.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 10, 47, 5, 1, 4, 'the body is dead because of sin', 'Connection of Life and Mortality', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between the mortal body and the life of the Spirit. Romans speaks of the body being dead due to sin, while 2 Corinthians discusses the desire for eternal life and the transformation from mortality to life.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 11, 47, 4, 14, 14, 'raised up Jesus', 'Resurrection Assurance in Paul', 'Both passages emphasize the resurrection of Jesus and the promise of believers'' resurrection. They highlight the role of God in raising Jesus and believers, linking the two events closely.', 'theme', 0.8459999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 11, 45, 6, 4, 5, NULL, 'Resurrection and New Life', 'Both passages emphasize the connection between Christ''s resurrection and the believer''s new life. Romans 8:11 speaks of being quickened by the Spirit, while Romans 6:4-5 discusses walking in newness of life after being raised with Christ.', 'theme', 0.727, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 11, 49, 1, 19, 20, 'raised up Jesus from the dead', 'Connection of Resurrection Power', 'Both passages emphasize the power of the Spirit in raising Jesus from the dead and its implications for believers. Romans highlights the indwelling Spirit that quickens mortal bodies, while Ephesians speaks of the mighty power that raised Christ and placed him in authority.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 11, 45, 8, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of the Spirit''s Role', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the Spirit of God dwelling in believers. Romans 8:9 states that having the Spirit is essential for belonging to Christ, while Romans 8:11 highlights the Spirit''s power to give life to mortal bodies.', 'theme', 0.608, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 11, 46, 6, 14, 14, 'raised up Jesus from the dead', 'Resurrection by God''s Power', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of resurrection through God''s power. Romans 8:11 speaks of the Spirit that raised Jesus, while 1 Corinthians 6:14 mentions God raising the Lord and believers.', 'theme', 0.594, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 11, 43, 5, 21, 21, 'quicken your mortal bodies', 'Resurrection and Quickening', 'Both passages emphasize the act of quickening the dead. Romans 8:11 speaks of the Spirit that raised Jesus, while John 5:21 highlights the Son''s authority to quicken whom he wills.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 11, 50, 3, 21, 21, 'quicken your mortal bodies', 'Resurrection and Transformation of Bodies', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation through the Spirit. Both passages emphasize the change of mortal bodies into a glorious state, linking the resurrection of Jesus to the future transformation of believers.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 12, 45, 6, 2, 15, 'to live after the flesh', 'Living Beyond the Flesh', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of being dead to sin and not living according to the flesh. Romans 8:12 states that we are debtors not to the flesh, while Romans 6:2-15 elaborates on how believers, having been baptized into Christ''s death, should walk in newness of life, rejecting sin.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 12, 46, 6, 19, 20, 'not to the flesh', 'Connection of Body and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of living not for the flesh but for God. Romans 8:12 speaks of not being debtors to the flesh, while 1 Corinthians 6:19-20 highlights that our bodies are God''s and should glorify Him.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 12, 60, 4, 2, 3, 'to live after the flesh', 'Living in the Flesh', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of not living according to the flesh. Romans 8:12 states we are debtors not to the flesh, while 1 Peter 4:2 mentions living no longer in the flesh to the lusts of men.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 12, 19, 116, 16, 16, NULL, 'Servanthood and Freedom from Bonds', 'This connection highlights the theme of servanthood and freedom from obligations. Romans 8:12 speaks of not being debtors to the flesh, while Psalms 116:16 expresses being loosed from bonds, indicating a transition from bondage to service.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 13, 48, 6, 8, 8, NULL, 'Connection of Flesh and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of living according to the flesh versus the Spirit. They highlight that sowing to the flesh leads to death or corruption, while sowing to the Spirit results in life.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 13, 60, 2, 11, 11, NULL, 'Connection of Fleshly Desires', 'Both passages emphasize the conflict between living according to the flesh and spiritual life. Romans 8:13 warns that living after the flesh leads to death, while 1 Peter 2:11 urges abstaining from fleshly lusts that war against the soul.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 8, 13, 46, 9, 27, 27, 'mortify the deeds of the body', 'Mortification of the Body', 'Both passages emphasize the need to control the body to achieve spiritual life. Romans speaks of mortifying the deeds of the body, while Corinthians highlights bringing the body into subjection.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
