(45, 10, 21, 60, 2, 8, 8, 'disobedient', 'Disobedience and Stumbling', 'Both passages emphasize disobedience among the people. Romans highlights God''s outreach to a ''disobedient'' people, while 1 Peter refers to those who ''stumble'' due to their disobedience.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 10, 21, 5, 9, 13, 13, 'disobedient', 'Disobedience and Stiffnecked People', 'Both passages emphasize the disobedience of Israel. Romans 10:21 refers to Israel as ''disobedient,'' while Deuteronomy 9:13 describes them as ''stiffnecked.'' This connection highlights a consistent theme of rebellion against God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
