(45, 11, 1, 28, 9, 17, 17, 'Hath God cast away his people?', 'God''s Relationship with Israel', 'Both passages emphasize God''s treatment of Israel. Romans 11:1 asserts that God has not cast away His people, while Hosea 9:17 indicates that God will cast them away for their disobedience.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 11, 2, 19, 94, 14, 14, 'cast away his people', 'God''s Faithfulness to His People', 'Both passages emphasize that God will not cast off His people. Romans 11:2 references God''s foreknowledge and intercession, while Psalms 94:14 reassures that He will not forsake His inheritance.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 11, 2, 45, 8, 29, 30, 'foreknew', 'Foreknowledge and Predestination', 'This connection highlights the concept of foreknowledge in both passages. Romans 11:2 speaks of God''s foreknowledge of His people, while Romans 8:29 emphasizes that those He foreknew are predestined.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
