(45, 11, 3, 16, 9, 26, 26, NULL, 'Prophets and Disobedience Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the killing of prophets as a sign of disobedience to God. Romans 11:3 reflects the lament of a prophet facing persecution, while Nehemiah 9:26 recounts the historical pattern of rebellion against God''s messengers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
