(45, 11, 4, 36, 1, 4, 4, NULL, 'Remnant and Idolatry Connection', 'Both passages emphasize a remnant that resists Baal worship. Romans highlights God''s preservation of faithful individuals, while Zephaniah speaks of cutting off the remnant of Baal. This connection highlights the theme of divine preservation amidst idolatry.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
