(45, 11, 36, 45, 16, 27, 27, 'to whom be glory for ever', 'Connection of Glory to God', 'Both passages emphasize giving glory to God. Romans 11:36 speaks of glory ''for ever,'' while Romans 16:27 highlights glory ''through Jesus Christ for ever.'' This connection highlights the consistent theme of glorifying God in relation to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 11, 36, 44, 17, 28, 28, 'of him, and through him, and to him', 'Connection of Divine Sustenance', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that all existence and life derive from God. Romans 11:36 speaks to God''s role in all things, while Acts 17:28 highlights living and moving in Him.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
