(45, 13, 14, 45, 8, 12, 13, 'make not provision for the flesh', 'Living by the Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not living according to the flesh. Romans 13:14''s call to ''make not provision for the flesh'' aligns with Romans 8:13''s warning that living after the flesh leads to death.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 13, 14, 62, 2, 15, 17, 'lusts thereof', 'Connection of Worldly Desires', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of worldly desires and the importance of living in accordance with God''s will. Romans 13:14 warns against fulfilling the flesh''s lusts, while 1 John 2:15-17 explicitly states that love for the world is incompatible with the love of the Father.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 14, 1, 45, 15, 1, 1, 'weak in the faith', 'Strength and Weakness in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the strong and the weak in faith. Romans 14:1 introduces the idea of receiving the weak, while Romans 15:1 calls on the strong to bear their infirmities.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 14, 1, 46, 8, 7, 13, 'weak in the faith receive ye', 'Connection of Weakness in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of considering the weak in faith and their conscience. Romans 14:1 advises receiving the weak without engaging in disputes, while 1 Corinthians 8:7-13 warns against causing them to stumble through knowledge. This connection highlights the responsibility of the stronger believers towards those who are weaker.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 14, 1, 46, 9, 22, 22, 'weak in the faith', 'Weakness and Acceptance in Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of accommodating the weak in faith. Both passages emphasize the importance of engaging with those who are weak to foster understanding and salvation.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
