(45, 14, 23, 46, 11, 29, 31, 'for whatsoever is not of faith is sin', 'Connection of Faith and Worthiness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of faith and discernment in actions related to eating. Romans highlights that actions not done in faith are sinful, while 1 Corinthians warns against unworthy participation in the Lord''s Supper, leading to serious consequences. This connection highlights the necessity of self-examination and faith in communal practices.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
