(45, 14, 23, 45, 14, 5, 5, 'whatsoever is not of faith is sin', 'Faith and Personal Conviction', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being fully persuaded in one''s own mind regarding personal beliefs and actions. Romans 14:23 highlights that actions not taken in faith are sinful, while Romans 14:5 encourages individuals to hold their convictions firmly.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(45, 14, 23, 45, 13, 2, 2, 'damned', 'Connection of Faith and Damnation', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of damnation for those who act against faith or authority. Romans 14:23 speaks of being damned for lack of faith, while Romans 13:2 discusses damnation for resisting God''s ordinance.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
